50|$|In July 2013, the Pennsylvania Department of Labor filed {{a federal}} lawsuit saying that Davison failed to <b>pay</b> <b>overtime</b> {{to at least}} 214 current and former sales representatives, arguing that Davison's {{business}} means they are covered by federal wage laws requiring them to do so. The lawsuit calls for Davison to start <b>paying</b> <b>overtime</b> and to <b>pay</b> employees' unpaid back wages.|$|R
