25|$|Ellerbe's tenure {{has been}} plagued by {{repeated}} scandal, including several involving his own hiring, but also uniform changes, higher <b>overtime</b> <b>pay,</b> new communication policy, charges of lying over how to count arson in the city, and retaliation against department employees. As of fall 2013, active controversies existed over fire engine and ambulance repair, the availability of vehicles for emergencies, and the location of vehicles.|$|E
